name: Larry S.
text:
My kids and I spent part of last week in Coloma Cottages, and we would highly recommend the Cottages. The location of the cottages is right on the river as advertised and the grounds of the cottages is very nice and comfortable for adults or kids. Also, the location is really just a 5 minute walk to the historic town, and very conveniently located for us to go rafting and enjoy the area.

The cottage we stayed in was the Rio Azul, and it was both very clean and comfortable for my family. The rooms and bedrooms were great and the kitchen was easy to cook dinner in.

I give them 5 stars.

name: Eric Rivera
text:
DO NOT STAY HERE! Pay an extra ten bucks and stay a couple of hotels down.

I have stayed at many Days Inns thru out the US. I find these Hotels to be a nice stay for the value. Usually clean rooms, good customer service, and clean linen. But this Hotel was dirty, Horrible customer service and dirty linen. The room was Hot and uncomfortable to sleep. The sheets were dirty with food spots and other soils. The Carpet was also dirty with spots. Wires were exposed in the wall.

I called to be changed to another room and they told me they couldn't because they were full, which was not true. I stayed here for three days and pre-paid and they wouldn't give me a refund. Next time I would totally pay an extra 10 bucks and stay at another hotel.

I will never stay at this hotel again and I do not recommend anybody else to stay here.

text: Must diagree with a fellow reviewer: the management was fine and we actually liked the breakfast. The pool was warm and relaxing. name: Steve Arias
text: Wow. This place is Run Down! Let me just start by saying we had reservations but when we checked in they said price went up...we were here on a big mountain bike event and there was no rooms available elsewhere. Beds were nasty and forced us to go to Wal-Mart and buy sleeping bags. Inside of the rooms are falling apart.. burn marks on comforters. Carpet looked like they were slashed with a blade. TV was super snowy and direct tv was a joke. Only one channel worked for us. Called reception and it rang another room. Also, seems like there is long term residents here. Outside of building is falling apart as well and seems like no one cleans at all. There was trash everywhere. Roof is falling apart and missing shingles. This place needs a major make over with large investment or a wrecking ball.

name: Miles Martin
text:
This place is dirty, no filthy, and the
entire property is littered with garbage and cigarette butts. I was there when The Monterey County Health Dept.had red tagged the pool, locked it with their pad lock and had put a big warning sign on the entrance to the pool and jaccuzzi.

The carpets are so dirty that your white socks get black just walking around the room after a short period of time.

Musty rooms with boken microwaves, wires hanging out, wrecked cars and PODS in the parking lot, cig burns in the blankets, lumpy pillows on old mattresses,  beer cans and trash found under the bed, bare bones breakfast lacking anything remotely good for you, suspect people roaming the parking lot at night, etc. etc, etc..

Even the staff laugh at what they're asking for the rooms !!

And the older Eastern Indian lady in the office had such a short fuse that when confronted with the health and safety violations on the property and overall cleanliness of the pool and property, she sent her punk ass husband out to to threaten to "kick my ass." Really ?

AVOID THIS PLACE !!!!

name: Brett Chik
text:
The hotel has been closed since December but reopened recently and we started on the first night it was open.

The good:
- The service was amazing. Everyone we interacted with had the utmost level of professionalism. The doormen greeted me by name each time we came and went which was a really nice touch.
- The room had an incredible view of the Bay.
- Room service was very quick.
- Staff was very fast to respond to the Four Seasons in-app messaging.
- Everything was clean and modern.
- The crab and shrimp omelette was delicious.
- Wireless charger and USB ports on the nightstand was a nice touch.

The bad:
- The was no in-room dining menu in our room nor any instructions on where to find one. We had to ask for a link to the menu.
- The coffee was absolutely terrible.  I‚Äôm not exaggerating when I say it was some the worst I have ever had my life.  After disliking it in one meal, they provided it complimentary in another meal but it was still quite bad. The problem likely isn‚Äôt the preparation but rather the selected beans. SF has a number of amazing roasters, they should seek out a better option from a local roaster.
- Doors slamming all morning long. I don‚Äôt know if it was Staff or guests, but from around 8 am too 11 am, doors near our room were constantly being opened and closed and quite loudly.  This woke me up and prevented me from getting as much sleep as I wanted to.  The doors need to be assisted so they close quietly.
- The toilet paper was completely awful, very thin and quite abrasive. This was so pretty surprising detail and I can‚Äôt begin to imagine how the product they were using would even be considered remotely up to their standards.

Overall, it wasn‚Äôt too bad but I don‚Äôt think it lived up to their reputation. I know they recently reopened and there are mistakes to be expected but something like low quality toilet paper doesn‚Äôt really have an excuse.  I hope this review will allow them the opportunity to make improvements where there are currently deficits.

I‚Äôm not sure I would stay there again at that price point given the above issues.

name: Yamami Studios
text:
Loews Regency San Francisco is a deluxe 5-star spa San Francisco city center hotel steps from Wells Fargo History Museum and within a short walk of Union Square. Staying here, you'll also be within a short walk of TransAmerica Pyramid and San Francisco Museum of Modern Art. This building is the third tallest in the city and offers a great view of the city.

The staff is amazing and friendly, ready to accommodate us for our every need.

This hotel has its own restaurant serving breakfast, lunch and dinner where you'll find a selection of items to try. Escape the stress of everyday life at The Spa, offering facials and body scrubs, as well as Swedish massages, deep-tissue massages and hot stone massages. Guests wishing to enjoy a drink will surely want to visit the bar/lounge.
In addition to the on-site spa, leisure facilities on offer include a 24-hour fitness center. Guests can make use of the free WiFi.

name: Guthrie Paterson
text: Great business hotel in the Financial District.  Rooms and service are great!  Also a good place for a breakfast meeting.

name: Md Sajjad Zahid
text:
Occupying the top 11 floors of a 48-floor high-rise in the Financial District, this contemporary, high-end hotel is a 5-minute walk from both the Embarcadero BART station and the Transamerica Pyramid.

Sophisticated, modern rooms feature 47-inch flat-screen TVs, iPod docks and Italian linens, plus picture windows offering views of the city or the Golden Gate Bridge. Upgraded rooms have marble bathrooms with separate tubs and showers. Suites add living rooms; some have terraces. There's 24-hour room service.

Amenities include a spa, a 24-hour business center and a gym, along with a warm bar and a polished brasserie serving Californian cuisine.

name: Mildred Griffin
text: We stayed 4 nights at the Loews Regency in the business district of San Francisco. We were greeted by the doorman and the front desk very warmly when we arrived. We were then taken to our room on the 47th floor with the most beautiful views on the bay from the Golden Gate Bridge, Sausilito, Alcatraz, to the lit up Bay Bridge. Unbelievable. The service at all levels is over the top and always with smiles. The best in SF and we have stayed all over SF the last 25 years We will be back

name: Brandon S
text:
The free breakfast consisted of recently thawed Eggo waffles... like still soggy levels of thaw just sitting out in the open. The fruit and bagels were decent enough but it felt more like a break room for employees than anything I'd consider to be for guests. No employees present, just a few guests, a few tables, and some snack foods tossed together.

The hand towel in the bathroom had a rather dark stain on it, I'm assuming from the last guest that put it back well enough the cleaning staff didn't bother checking. The overall cleanliness of the room was suspect...I found hair in the bed that wasn't mine.

Overall for what it cost for the night it was adequate, if the above doesn't bother you of course.

name: Lisa F
text: Friendly staff, good location away from the craziness of the convention center. I found the room to be clean with a nice big fridge and comfy bed. The lights freaked me out a few times until I figured out how to turn the sensors off. An important thing to know about this area is it gets very loud outside on the weekend nights, there is a billiard hall and a couple nightclubs with loud people and motorcycles. If you want to get any sleep friday or saturday night before 2am bring earplugs and tylenol pm. Across the street from the front desk there is a bakery that has the most amazing cream puffs and other treats. You can't beat the free parking, that is what always brings me back here during conventions, they lock the parking lot up at night for anyone who doesn't have a key so I felt safe walking back to my room after dark.

name: TJ Taylor
text:
This is a wonderful hotel with a beautiful view of a lake.  The staff is very friendly and the cleaning of the rooms are daily.  The rooms are spacious and business grade.  You have free wi-fi, ice, central heating/air, clean linen, adjustable beds (sleep number), coffee maker, alarm clock radio, hair dryer, shampoo, conditioner, lotion and soap.  The view of the lake was grand with a fountain, geese on the water, a Koi fish pond with it's own fountain and a nice pathway.  The hotel also has a swimming pool with a safety fence a small amphitheater area with soft music coming through speakers when not in use. There are ice rooms located around the property with soda machines.

The convention rooms are elegant and host many events. There is a Grill that serves and offers room service, a Bar but my favorite is the dining room.  The breakfasts were fresh cooked daily whether it was served or buffet and refilled often.  The morning servers along with the chef and cooks were very friendly and personable. They were my favorite part of the experience not excluding Sylvia at the front desk.

The rooms are very clean along with their bathrooms. Because of the fear of bed bugs in some of the local motels and extended stay hotels this was a pleasant experience. alleviating those concerns. All concerns are addressed immediately (not that there should be any but things can happen).

Do be aware that during the wet season it tended to flood in front of the entrance to the hotel's property. (This might have been addressed by now)

This hotel is a definite Yes and a Must Try.

Rooms are reasonably large with sleep number beds and the standard ameneties. Good front desk and huskeeping staff. They need to infuse some cash to upgrade it to competative hotels in the area. The hotel is in a strange area but it very close to to downtown, Arden Fair, business 80 freeway and lots of restaurants and shopping. The hotel is a good value, but needs some work.

text:
I wasn't sure what to expect with the price and some of the reviews I read.  However, I was very pleasantly surprised by how cute it is and how nice the room was.  Sure, it's an older motel so the bathrooms aren't luxurious or big, but the room itself was very nice with the laminate wood floor and updated furniture.  It felt clean and modern.

For the price and quality I fully recommend this place to everyone looking for a low cost way to have a place in Palm Springs.  If you don't need the big pool vibe and just want a clean, pretty place to sleep you cannot go wrong here.

name: Lisa H.
text: This hotel was fantastic. It is a small property, but the staff is super friendly and helpful. The pool area is so relaxing... It is located in a great location. The rooms are newly renovated, really well maintained, and very clean.

name: Roy Steele
text:
I had a three night stay at The Monroe Palm Springs. I wasn't familiar with this three star hotel in North Palm Springs, and stumbling upon it was pure luck on my part.  The check in was quick and easy, and the front desk staff were efficient and friendly. They were able to answer my questions about the hotel and restaurants in the immediate vicinity. This is a limited service hotel as they don't have a restaurant on property.

I had a room with a king sized bed at the back of the property. The room was spacious, the bed and pillows were comfortable, the wifi was adequate, and the bathroom was clean. I didn't leave the a/c on when I wasn't in the room, so most importantly, the air conditioning was fantastic and cooled the room quickly. I also appreciated the large HDTV.

The pool area and jacuzzi faces south, so it's perfect for sun bathing.

This old Ramada Inn was renovated by the current owner, and they did a brilliant job. The interior designers transformed this tired chain hotel into a unique and hip boutique hotel. I would stay at The Monroe Palm Springs again without hesitation.

name: Dana Chef
text:
Although they are going through renovations,  the rooms were clean and nice. The staff was friendly and accommodating!
I came for a quiet, relaxing getaway, and met my objective!

text: I luv luv luv luv this place. Super cute inside and out. It was the hilton a few years back and a days inn before that. I think its going to change owners again but either way the name may change often but its always been a nice clean friendly warm comfortable place throughout the years.

name: Chris Jefferson
text: I would not recommend that anyone stay here. Not one thing was correct during my time at the hotel.  There was insufficient parking.  I did not get the room I requested.  The widely advertised remodel had only taken place in a few rooms, not in all of them as they would have you believe, and my bed was broken....yeah.

name: Mary Falls
text:
We stayed for two days during the week.
The good - The room was nice. The bed was comfortable and the pillows were fluffy.
The bad - The ice machine was broken the whole time we were there. The staff told us to walk to 7 eleven if we needed ice. The jacuzzi was broken. The staff said it would be fixed the day we checked out. There were fire ants in the pool area and when we let the staff know, all that was said was "oh great. I'll let maintenance know." There was really only one staff member that was worth remembering.

In our opinion, this is not a place that is very accommodating. If you just need a place to sleep, this is the place.

name: Jared Brier
text: Good value. Nice clean room. Only spent one night for a place to sleep. Didn't see around the property much.

text:
Basic hotel in the Northern part of Palm Springs, with easy access to Downtown (5 mins by car). We liked our comfortable beds and the cleanliness of the rooms.

We did not get to try the pool as we only stayed one night and arrived pretty late. If you consider this hotel for your stay in Palm Springs make sure to check coupon websites before booking as they seem to offer a Groupon every once in awhile. Without discount the room rate is a little bit over what you'd expect to pay for a standard two-story hotel.

name: Michael Thomson
text:
I have stayed at many hotels around the world, having worked for The Four Seasons Hotels and Resorts for many years in management.  I know what a value is when I see it.  Due to a fire in my home I needed a place to stay.  Having lived in Palm Springs for over 20 years, I watched as this hotel like most things in Palm Springs was brought back to life.  I never imagined it would be so nice and at such a great price.  Beats the heck out of Motel 6.  Better ptice, much nicer room, free wifi ($2.99 a day at Motel 6) and a free breakfast.  Not just a contintal breakfast or just coffee, but a real breakfast.  In a real restaurant with real servers and some of the best food in town.  Rick's has always been a favorite of my Late husband and myself.  If you are even thinking of staying anywhere else, STOP, look and listen, this is THE only place hands down.
Michael Thomson

text:
My stay was extremely pleasant. I was only suppose to stay for 4 days however, my stay turned into two weeks.
Being that my reservations were for only 4 days they were able to find me a room for the remaining of my stay. The first room was big and roomy. Room 205. The second room had a balcony which the view was beautiful. Lush green trees, peaceful, Room 209.  What I really appreciated so much is that they allowed me to take care of my mom's service dog. My mom fractured her hip and could not take care of her pooch. I explained the situation and they allowed me to bring my mom's pooch to stay with me. They were so understanding, it was incredible, and meant so much to both my mom and myself. This really goes above and beyond. All of the staff are so nice. I would highly  recommend this hotel. This is the only hotel I will ever stay in when I am in Sebastopol.

name: Christopher Matthews
text:
In short, this is an overpriced 2 star hotel.

We stayed on the ground floor. The room was nicer than Motel 6, but not $200/night nicer. Neighbors doors could be heard closing. Upstairs neighbors sounded lime a herd of elephants. Parking is bizarre, being underground and not well lit, plus no elevator from the bottom. For the money, you might expect more than plastic-wrapped grocery store danishes, bad coffee, apple and orange juices, toast, and apples and oranges. Maybe should have cereal, cocoa, more fruit options, yogurts, bagels, etc. Half the electrical plugs wouldn't hold the pins for our phone chargers amd the plugs are difficult to get to. No pool.

On the plus side, it's four blocks from the beach and across the street from the San Francisco Zoo and just a couple miles to the VA Medical Center. The beds aren't high end, but they are relatively comfortable. It's probably worth $100/night, but that's it.

name: Rose Deleonardo
text:
Isn't near the San Francisco sites most people want to see. We had to take an Uber back & forth. It didn't have an elevator to the upper floors, so you have to lug your suitcases up &down stairs by yourself. Complimentary breakfast exists solely of coffe, tea, juice & packaged danishes. Even 1/2 of the toaster didn't work. There's no main room to eat, so you have to juggle your food & drink up the stairs to your room or make several trips.
The manager Amy, who's probably a relative, was arrogant & rude on several occasions to my sister-in-law.

name: Chef Stevie B
text: This is my absolute favorite place to stay in Palm Springs. The owners Rick and Rob greet you with a hug and know you by your name upon check in. The resort is very clean, relaxing and a whole lot of fun.  Continental breakfast is served daily with a variety of cereals, muffins, donuts, breakfast bars, milk, coffee, bananas, oatmeal, etc. Since I‚Äôm a foodie, my favorite part of the resort is during a 3 day weekend stay, they do a bbq for the entire resort. It gives everyone a chance to mingle, hang out, eat, drink and just have a great time. I also enjoy the fact that Rick comes out, hangs out with the guests and chats with us.

name: George Maynor
text: Just spent 5 wonderful days. Large, spacious rooms nicely done. Ours included a full kitchen. Recently upgraded grounds are very relaxing. Our hosts took great care to see to our needs. If you are looking for a men's resort close to everything,  this should be your destination!

name: Anthony Minier (DJ AnthonyM)
text: This is a very comfortable enclosed gay men's resort. It is surrounded by high walls and the entry is through the check-in area so the owners (they live onsite) maintain some control over who is coming and going. This makes it one of the more mellow and quite resorts in this area and unless you are in your early 20's, you will appreciate the relaxed and easy going pace of this resort. The residences (studio's and suites) are in older buildings but they are well maintained and the whole complex has a certain charm to it. I have stayed here 3 times over the past so many years and have always enjoyed my visit immensely. They have a nice outdoor pool area which is clothing optional which also makes the high walls that surround the resort more useful since families driving by with children in their cars will not get an eyeful. There is a very large Jacuzzi as well. If you are gay and are visiting Palm Springs but the thought of the larger less intimate resorts that are often packed with a boisterous younger crowd don't quite appeal to your idea of a relaxing getaway, by all means try to book a room here. They are often fully booked since it is on the smaller side but you will be happy you stayed here if you book far enough in advance (or off season).

name: smith Aaron
text: My boyfriend and I stayed here for our trip out to LA and we couldn't have chosen a better place to stay. We stayed in the Abbot Kinney Suite, and it was a great experience. The suite had an open separate bedroom with desk and dresser with night tables on each side and a living room with a fire place. There was a cute kitchen with a deep sink and a claw foot tub and nicely tiled bathroom. The suite had windows everywhere and had massive amounts of sunlight. When you stepped out there was a balcony that overlooked Rose Ave and Venice Beach. (BEAUTIFUL) We sat our there often drinking and enjoying the view and atmosphere of Venice. The staff and owner were super nice and accommodating. The street was semi busy during the day and quite at night. There is a lot of restaurants around and the boardwalk is only steps away. The street parking was great. We always found a spot in front of the hotel. We came there to visit all of LA but just ended up stay in the area and keeping The Rose as our home base. Totally recommend staying here if you want to be away from all the crazy of the city and live like a local.

For 200+USD I think this is not very worth it. Next time in Venice Beach I'll try a different hotel.

name: Matthew Morgan
text: Was reluctant to book here, due to other reviews.  Was pleasantly surprised.  Although you can tell that the rooms are old, they have done a respectable job renovating the rooms.  The heart shaped Jacuzzi is an awesome feature and it is big enough to comfortably accommodate two people.  The rooms were clean. New carpet and beds would make a big difference. Overall we were satisfied for the price we paid.  Microwave, refrigerator and a flat screen TV were nice new renovations.  The imitation fireplace was a very nice touch, had realistic animated flames and it put out some really good heat.  Was happy that there was a CVS and a Savemart next door and another great restaurant right down by the lake. (you can even see the lake from your back window upstairs).  If you are looking for a place that is kept clean for a good price, with a quaint atmosphere, this is where you should book.  We booked on Orbitz and saved a bundle with a coupon.

text: Excellent staff. Silverfish were friendly. Electronic locks on the room doors didn't work in half the rooms. Could use some vending machines. Family owned. name: Laurie Swanson
text: Thankfully we only needed the room for the night. We are California residents doing business nearby and decided stay for the evening rather than fight the rush hour traffic back to San Diego. The O.C Fair has caused rooms to be limited. The only reason I am succumbing to posting a negative review is to perhaps save someone who has saved long for a vacation from utter disappointment! The owners of this establishment should be ashamed of not only the run down but  the filthy condition of their establishment. When entering the first room assigned to us we found it had not even been cleaned from the previous occupants! Potato chips strewn all over the floor, soiled bed and other debris strewn throughout the room. They upgraded us. Laughable. Keep in mind I do not mind staying at the Super 8 for overnights, I do not require the Ritz Carlton for practical matters. The upgrade to the "suite" the kitchen had a missing cabinet door, one of the two, broken glass in the Windows, the entry door had been kicked in and poorly patched and everything was disgustingly dirty, coffee table hasn't been wiped down in 20 years kind of grime! Just saying. And Im being nice.

text:

The motel looks a bit run-down and does not attract the most trusted guests because of the price. Room was ok, the bed was clean, the carpet unfortunately not. So we'll spend a few dollars more next time.

name: Julie Dawson-Parlee
text: If you just need a budget option near LAX, Super 8 is great! Attractive building, remodeled rooms, outdoor pool, comfortable cushioned mattresses and soft pillows, simple but adequate breakfast, located near the rental car lots in a pretty safe area. If you don‚Äôt need amenities and can overlook some scratched paint on the doors and cosmetic flaws on the walls, you‚Äôll be happy here.

name: Suava Man
text: Great rooms with a nice modern look. Not too much noise due to its location near the airport. Staff is great and the beds are superb. I didn't get to check out the stores in the surrounding area but I've heard good things. This is a cozy spot for someone that doesn't want to be too far from LAX and the freeway, definitely worth the money.

name: David Amitai
text: This pillows were terrible, I barely slept. The AC was all or nothing, I couldn't find a happy medium. A lot of basic things were missing, like the bathroom didn't have a towel bar. The floor appeared clean but after walking on it in white socks for a few min my socks were dirty. I came here to save money. My advice: spend a little extra to get a better place so that you can rest comfortably!

name: Armando Parra
text: Best Greek Restaurant inside. Ever! I couldn't believe it. Worst location but the MODT INCREDIBLE Greek Food. Its a must.

name: Ben Lux
text: I appreciate the staff here. I've been going here for years on a monthly basis. The rooms have no carpet, it's recently updated. I appreciate that. BUT, there's no microwave in the rooms. You have to go to the lobby. It doesn't bug me none. It's just different than most.
resp: {'time': 1575260710667, 'text': 'Thank you for taking time and sharing your wonderful experience. My team will be very happy to know, their service was appreciated and will motivate them more. We look forward to having you back again, and enjoy our hospitality.'}

name: Pam Tabor
text: I was pleasantly surprised! I would stay here again.

name: Chadell Hardwick (Angry Chef)
text: The room was had a funny smell. The front desk lady was beyond rude. The grounds are littered with cigarettes buts and cigar wrappers. Two fights broke out over night and the dog that wouldn't stop barking. For the money it wasn't worth it. The rude staff lumpy bed sealed the deal.

name: Xplicit Suizyd
text: Great hotel. Great location. The rooms are clean. The rooms have a refrigerator. The rooms are bug free. They offer free breakfast and wifi. The airport is near by and the hotel offers free shuttle rides to the airport when you are leaving town. 711 is two blocks down from the hotel and lots of restaurants are right down the street from there. It's a great location. Homeless people are pretty much non-existent at this location. I will definitely visiting this location again and really soon. Best rapper alive.

name: GTA Player
text: This place is cool. They have free breakfast and the rooms are very clean. You won‚Äôt enjoy your stay here if you are annoyed by the planes that fly overhead but you they don‚Äôt make too much noise. Overall this is a good place to stay in.

name: Robert Truxal
text: Great value. Very good free breakfast. Nice rooms.

name: Natalie McManus
text: A bit old, definitely not in perfect condition, but good parking considering the area. Easy check in/out. Very comfortable bed. We had room 123, which is right next to the exit gate. It was pretty loud each time someone left. Very close to LAX and I would stay here again if I have any early flight.

name: Bill Tzetzos
text:
If I could give a zero, I would... Paper thin walls and directly under an LAX runway... What a dive. We can hear the people above and on either side. The next door shower sounds like it's in our bedroom.
Why bother renovating this dive. A waste of redecorating dollars.  @Wyndham... Drop this place and your overall rating will go up significantly. I'm actually thinking of dropping Wyndham as a chain where I may stay.

name: Michael Goodman
text: Very nice rooms.  Newly renovated.  Parking is hard due to limited space.  Nice breakfast setup.

name: Abraham Williams
text: Realized I had no towels, soap or toilet paper in my room after check in, had to pick it up at the front desk.

name: Zach Dorland
text: A little shady looking on the outside but an overall acceptable hotel to stay 1 quick night. The airplane traffic stopped around 11pm the night we were there. My kids (ages 4,6,&8) loved watching the jets come in to land every 5 minutes others may not enjoy it so much.

name: Katiria Perez
text: Got a nice clean room here. Will definitely stay again.

name: April Rorie
text: Clean, comfortable and stylish!!  Reasonably priced. Staff is super friendly! Would definitely stay there again.

name: April Rorie
text: Clean, comfortable and stylish!!  Reasonably priced. Staff is super friendly! Would definitely stay there again.

name: Micha≈Ç Skowron
text:
The motel is located about 2.5 km from the airport. Every minute or so there's a plane flying almost above your head. Fortunately, the noise isn't that bad when inside the room. The surroundings aren't really interesting.
The room is clean has a big, comfortable bed. It's equipped with an ironing board, iron, flat-screen TV with cable, quite big fridge, mini coffee machine. The bathroom is clean. You get towels, free toiletries and a hair dryer. The room is much better than the overall look and feel of the motel (which is average). The staff is rather nice and helpful. They have a swimming pool but I didn't have a chance to use it.
Breakfast is mediocre. But the add-water-and-stir oatmeal and coffee weren't bad.
Overall impression - a decent place for one or two nights, especially when you travel for several hours and you want sth close to the airport, with a comfortable bed.

name: henk van albrecht
text: Had a non smoking room, but the first thing I smelled when i came in the room was smoke. So that was kinda weird. Parking also it's much small, no room to back out, or drive, we had to park on the street.

Expensive compared to what you get. So no, you don't get what you pay for apparently...

text: Bad experience. Reserved room through TA. When arrived they said rate was for smoking room, wanted a $20 upcharge to non-smoking. 2nd day their workers started tearing everything out of nextdoor room at 6:30 am, extremely loud.  Lasted 2 days. They moved us 4 doors down because our room was next in line. Lobby staff were very impersonal. I had to go through Wyndham to get a $43 credit back, which just got me back to my quoted rate. Motel management refused to give me any reward points to compensate for remodeling inconvenience. Planes go over every 3 minutes. At least this stops from 10:30 pm until 6:30 am.  Highly NOT recommended!

text: The reservations got "lost" by the hotel, they were rude, demanding, sketchy area. If you like people that are rude or don't understand you go here.

name: BECKY JENSEN
text: Check in was quick and easy. We had to leave a $50 cash deposit which was annoying bc I had to borrow cash from my sister as I didn't have it on hand. The room was decent and upgraded (fresh paint, granite in bathroom, flat screen TV). My sisters room smelled like smoke and a guy came to help us switch us rooms for her. They tried arguing it was a non-smoking room. Whatever room it is, someone smoked in there and they're not sleeping in that. We went to the pool, they were various degrees heated, one looked murky but we avoided it and had a good time. At night I constantly heard people coming up and down the stairs. It was so noisy. Lots of tweakers up and about. The website said breakfast was included but when we got to the lobby it was only coffee. At 11 someone knocked on our door seeing if we were checking out. Moments later at checkout, the front desk radios the guy walking around to physically check our room before giving the deposit back. I just felt like the whole time the hotel was trying to cover their butt and not really caring about the guest. But we checked out fine, got our deposit back and left. Side note: when we called to reserve directly with the hotel they charge $100 more than doing it online.

text: Looks uninviting on the outside, but the room was completely renovated and ok.  The bed wasn't that comfortable though.

name: Tim Newton
text: I would really like to say allot of nice things about this place but I can't think of a whole lot. About the only nice thing was the gal at check in and her hospitality. The room was very big had all the amenities as posted. But there was some kind of stench about it like backed up sewage or something. I was hoping that with time it would dissipate. However, i ended up going to buy some Lysol disinfectant and that only seemed to help for a short while then there smell came back. Luckily i take a sleeping pill so I was able to sleep early. But I was awakened by the sounds of semis in the parking lot at around 2:30. I could not get back to sleep so I stepped out to smoke a cigarette. When I went back inside room I turned the heater on. Once I did that the smoke detector went off. Funny how no one from front desk even came to check on the room. I was finally able to reach the detector and turn it off myself. I decided to start packing but was too tired. I finally got to sleep at around 6:30 am and slept for couple hours. I was afraid I was going to oversleep and be charged an extra night. Thank God I got out. I usually try to avoid places like motel 6 but any motel 6 would be like a palace compared to this place.  I am no snob by any means and I don't have a very big travel account but i would skimp on other things to be able to afford a nicer hotel. I do not recommend this place at all, obviously.

name: Ashley Juarez
text:
We were locked in to our hotel for half an hour and missed out reservations to a restaurant we booked a month in advance to get to. It ruined our night. Even worse when we came back to the hotel , that same door was left unlocked so anyone could enter our hotel and a couple was trapped in elevator. I called the staff and they were completely clueless and no help at all. Worst experience ever in a hotel and this is very dangerous given we were not able to properly exit the hotel. If your building were to ever catch on fire, everyone would be trapped with no way to escape.

Elevator not working -guest service told me to call them back in 5 minutes which is completely unacceptable
Door unable to be opened-my friend called the guest service and he had a horrible attitude. After telling him that no-one is able to open the door from the outside or inside he responded snidely with : its a matter of turning the knob.
resp:
{'time': 1573672486755, 'text': 'Hello Ashley,
I am very sorry you experienced this inconvenience. We had an issue with the bolt on the lock, and I completely understand your concern. I cannot find your name as a guest, but please reach out to us direct. I would like to apologize personally.
Thank you,
Charlena'}

name: Israel Carberry
text: I come to SD once a year for work, and this is my go-to place to stay.  Completely self-serve, but you can request just about anything you need.  Only con is their body wash; I bring my own soap.
resp: {'time': 1549667165035, 'text': 'Thanks for leaving feedback, we are so glad you enjoy your stays with us! We look forward to your next visit to San Diego.'}

name: Mitch Collins
text: A unique place in the heart of the Gas Lamp district. Cool rooms, great value, nice location.
resp: {'time': 1562954958674, 'text': 'Hi Mitch,\nThanks for leaving feedback about your stay! We are so glad to hear you enjoyed your stay with us.  We would love to welcome you back to our center of Gaslamp location the next time you are in town!'}

name: Jonathan
text: Great place to stay right in the heart of down town. The place is very clean felt like home. Only down side is that if your not out late the noise is notice able if your trying to get an early night rest.
resp: {'time': 1564505413128, 'text': 'Hi Jonathan,\nThanks fro the review, and for staying with us! We love your comment, "felt like home". I will share this with our staff. We would love to welcome you back in one of our quieter, rear facing rooms! Thanks again!'}

name: Todd Warren
text: For the money, it is a decent stay. In the heart of the gas lamp district which is nice if you are looking to bar hop. The entrance is kinda hidden, you have to park up the street at a parking garage. it is $15 a day. Our room was clean. We had the studio on the 3rd floor.  be prepared, It is loud! there is a club right next door so there is music going late. bring ear plugs if you have trouble sleeping in that environment. I have a noise machine so I had no problem. Complaints, elevator is obnoxiously loud. the entry way floors are dirty. If you are looking to save a couple hundred of dollars on your stay, it is a good option. I would stay again.
resp: {'time': 1562955137611, 'text': 'Hi Todd,\nThanks so much for staying with us and for leaving feedback. We are glad you liked our location in the center of the lively Gaslamp district. With the busy 5th Ave right outside our door, we do get street noise, though we provide ear plugs in all of our rooms. I will share your feedback with our staff. Thanks again for staying, we hope to welcome you back again!'}

name: Dr. Monkey
text: We stayed the weekend at this quaint studio apt. It is kind of a cross between a hotel and a hostel. There's a modern, clean private bathroom. Kitchenette with microwave, two stovetop burners, sink, and fridge. Location is spot on! Right in the heart of the Gaslamp Quarter. It's right above a Cuban restaurant so we were concerned about possible noise but even though you could hear music in the stairwell and hallway once you're in the room...peace and quiet. Would recommend.
resp: {'time': 1564505079049, 'text': 'Thanks so much for staying with us and for providing feedback. We are glad you enjoyed our amenities and central location. We would love to welcome you back on your next visit to San Diego!'}

name: allan balangue
text: There's no parking here. Nest on Fifth told us to use Park it on Market but neglected to tell us to make a reservation for parking. The receptionist basically told us we're on our own.
resp:
{'time': 1573672767248, 'text': 'Hi Allan,
Thanks for staying with us and for leaving feedback. Since we are in the center of the Gaslamp district, parking can be a little difficult to come by. We try to offer suggestions in the emails we send prior to arrival.
Although I understand you had frustrations finding parking, I hope you found the location of the apartment convenient and enjoyed your stay.
Thanks again for choosing Nest on Fifth!'}

name: Edward Murphy
text: Nest on Fifth is a quaint, cute little place in the middle of all the action in the Gaslamp district. We stayed in a room for a couple of nights. Fortunately, the building is within walking distance of a bunch of great bars, a CVS, and restaurants. Our room had a kitchenette, which is great for days when we didn't feel like eating out. Some things we didn't like so much were the loud noises from the surrounding bars and the lack of parking. But we appreciate that ear plugs were supplied. There is a parking structure nearby, but it is not free. We did stay here right before Comicon, so parking was difficult to find. Also, keep in mind that the rooms are like studio apartments. We didn't mind this, but just know that you'd be cooking and sleeping in the same room. Overall, I'd recommend Nest on Fifth if you are fairly young and enjoy the San Diego night life.
resp: {'time': 1573672924435, 'text': 'Hi Edward,\nWe appreciate you leaving us a comprehensive review. We are so glad you enjoyed our neighborhood and amenities. We also have 1 bedroom apartments, in the case you want to spread out a little or invite extra guests next time! We would love to welcome you back.\nThanks again for the great review and for choosing Nest on Fifth!'}

name: Riverapr 21
text: It's smack in the middle. Full kitchen which is a big plus
resp: {'time': 1564504987546, 'text': 'Thanks for the review and for staying with us Richard. So glad you enjoyed our central location!'}

text: Great location, great rooms
resp: {'time': 1562955263298, 'text': "Hi Mahdi,\nThanks so much for leaving feedback. We are glad you enjoyed our downtown, 'center of it all' location! We would love to welcome you back someday soon!"}
